Usage:
./pe_dump [-i nic] [-r pcap_file] -d dump_dir [-f "pcap_filter"] [-L lru_cache_size] [-K max_pe_file_size (KB)] [-D debug_level] [-A]

-i : Capture packets at network interface (e.g., eth0)
-r : Read packets from file
-d : directory where PE files will be downloaded
-f : BPF filter
-L : size of the LRU cache that holds the reassembled TCP flows 
-K : used to limit the size of the PE files to be collected
-D : print debugging messages at different levels of verbouseness
-A : if present, client IP addresses will not be anonymized

